body:
This is a new one(for me that is), I had queued up for a match, gotten through bans and champ select and instead of loading I get a black screen with an eventual prompt box saying: "Unable to connect to the server. Please check your network connection and attempt to reconnect to your game."

I have "checked my connection", fiddled with my firewall, and attempted to run in various compatibility/admin modes and all to no avail. The match is probably over now, which is irritating for a multitude of reasons but the most pressing concern is that the client has not given me any options or reverted to a "not in game" state.  Any help would be appreciated .
 {{sticker:slayer-jinx-unamused}}

replies.body:
Earlier this morning we noticed that a widespread issue was causing players to be disconnected before seeing the loading screen. We've been working on the issue, which should be resolved at this time, but you can keep up to date on the matter by checking the post [**here**](http://boards.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/c/help-support/3Lmbjp8Y-3132017-na-server-issues).

We're on the job to address this issue as fast as we can!
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
